Reasoning: The paper focuses on the application of learning-based approaches to perception and decision-making in autonomous robot systems, which falls under the category of Robotics (cs.RO). The paper also extensively covers deep learning-based methods of environment perception and understanding, including monocular depth estimation, object detection, and semantic segmentation, which are subfields of Computer Vision (cs.CV) and Machine Learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses navigation methods based on reinforcement learning, which falls under the category of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Systems and Control (cs.SY).
